Project Title: Food Website

Description:

This project showcases a visually appealing and informative food website, featuring a variety of culinary content, recipes, and restaurant recommendations.

Features:

Responsive Design: The website adapts seamlessly to different screen sizes, ensuring optimal viewing on desktops, tablets, and smartphones.
Recipe Database: A comprehensive collection of recipes with detailed instructions, ingredient lists, and nutritional information.
Restaurant Reviews: User-generated reviews and ratings for local restaurants, covering cuisine types, ambiance, and service.
Food Blog: Engaging articles on food trends, cooking tips, and cultural insights.
Interactive Elements: Features like search functionality, recipe categorization, and social media integration.
Technologies Used:

HTML: Structure of the webpage.
CSS: Styling and layout of the website.
JavaScript: Enhancing user experience with interactive elements (e.g., search functionality, recipe categorization).
Framework (optional): Consider using a popular framework like React, Vue, or Angular for a faster development process and pre-built components.
Getting Started:

Clone the Repository:
Bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/food-website.git
Use code with caution.

Install Dependencies: If using a framework or additional libraries, install them according to their instructions.
Run a Local Server: Use a local development server (e.g., Python's built-in http.server or a tool like npm run dev) to view the website in your browser.
Customization:

Content: Replace the placeholder content with your own recipes, restaurant reviews, and blog articles.
Design: Customize the CSS styles to match your desired aesthetic.
Functionality: Add or modify features based on your specific requirements (e.g., user registration, recipe saving).
